1
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,600
Are you Yingrong's mother?

2
00:00:38,759 --> 00:00:40,000
Oh, you're not.

3
00:00:42,159 --> 00:00:43,799
Doesn't Wang Yingrong live here?

4
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:44,759
You're looking for Wang Yingrong?

5
00:00:44,759 --> 00:00:47,200
Aren't you here for our Zheng Xiaochuan?

6
00:00:47,439 --> 00:00:48,479
That's right.

7
00:00:48,479 --> 00:00:49,159
It was clearly me...

8
00:00:49,159 --> 00:00:51,079
...who saved your Fang family's daughter, Fang Fang.

9
00:00:51,479 --> 00:00:53,399
You should be here to thank me.

10
00:00:53,439 --> 00:00:55,240
We should thank Sister Wang Yingrong.

11
00:00:55,479 --> 00:00:57,000
She was the one who saved my sister that day.

12
00:00:57,119 --> 00:00:58,640
I saw it clearly.

13
00:01:06,359 --> 00:01:07,239
Sis!

14
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,319
Sister!

15
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:11,680
Sis!

16
00:01:13,359 --> 00:01:14,599
Sister!

17
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:18,079
The reason we came today...

18
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:19,400
...is to find Wang Yingrong.

19
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,200
There's no mistake.

20
00:01:20,439 --> 00:01:21,879
You must be mistaken.

21
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,920
It was clearly me who pulled her up.

22
00:01:24,319 --> 00:01:25,480
Sister!

23
00:01:26,159 --> 00:01:27,599
Sister!

24
00:01:32,239 --> 00:01:33,000
Sister!

25
00:01:37,519 --> 00:01:38,159
Sister Yingrong!

26
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:38,760
Sis.

27
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:40,239
Sis, are you okay?

28
00:01:40,239 --> 00:01:40,959
Sis.

29
00:01:41,719 --> 00:01:42,799
So...

30
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:43,560
...it was clearly me...

31
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,159
...who saved your daughter Fang Fang.

32
00:01:45,959 --> 00:01:46,920
What's going on?

33
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,519
I'm not sure.

34
00:01:47,519 --> 00:01:49,480
You only gave my sister a hand at the very end.

35
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,439
If earlier on...

36
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,280
...Wang Yingrong hadn't saved my sister...

37
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,000
...my sister wouldn't have made it.

38
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,040
Besides...

39
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,560
...even if you hadn't come...

40
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,400
...I could have pulled my sister up myself.

41
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,200
So it really was Yingrong who saved her.

42
00:02:01,239 --> 00:02:01,640
No, no.

43
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,799
It wasn't like that.

44
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:04,239
I was by the river that day too.

45
00:02:04,239 --> 00:02:05,400
I saw our Xiaochuan...

46
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,760
...saving your Fang Fang.

47
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,280
Ma'am.

48
00:02:07,599 --> 00:02:08,560
Your boy...

49
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:10,039
...did indeed at the very end...

50
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,560
...give my Fang Fang a hand.

51
00:02:12,439 --> 00:02:14,560
So I'll say thanks for that here.

52
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:15,240
Thank you.

53
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:15,919
Thank you.

54
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,280
Just words?

55
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,240
Where's the gift?

56
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:19,759
Sister Wang!

57
00:02:19,759 --> 00:02:21,639
Why are you still washing clothes?

58
00:02:21,639 --> 00:02:22,199
Come quick!

59
00:02:22,199 --> 00:02:23,520
Someone is looking for your second child.

60
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,080
Hurry!

61
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,719
You must be Wang Yingrong's mother.

62
00:02:28,719 --> 00:02:30,159
Thank you, Big Sister.

63
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:32,479
Thanks to your daughter saving my Fang Fang.

64
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,400
Otherwise my Fang Fang would have lost her life.

65
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,520
Oh, right.

66
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:36,479
Since it's our first visit...

67
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,319
...a small token.

68
00:02:37,319 --> 00:02:38,000
Take it back.

69
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,159
Don't be polite, don't be a stranger.

70
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,159
Yingrong is back.

71
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,159
Wang Yingrong is back.

72
00:02:48,639 --> 00:02:49,840
What kind of person is that?

73
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,400
Reeking of fish.

74
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:53,639
You must be Comrade Wang Yingrong.

75
00:02:56,319 --> 00:02:57,120
Thank you.

76
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,560
For saving me in the river last time.

77
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,840
Oh, it's you.

78
00:03:02,199 --> 00:03:03,000
It was nothing.

79
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,000
It was no trouble at all.

80
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,400
Anyone else would have done the same.

81
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:06,840
Please don't worry about it.

82
00:03:07,159 --> 00:03:08,919
I can never repay you for saving my life.

83
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:11,400
That motorcycle over there...

84
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:13,560
...is just a small token of our appreciation.

85
00:03:13,639 --> 00:03:14,680
I can't accept this.

86
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,599
It's too expensive.

87
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,240
You must accept it.

88
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,080
This should be for my third son.

89
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,400
It belongs to our Xiaochuan.

90
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,400
It was my Xiaochuan who saved your daughter.

91
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,439
Give it here.

92
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:26,080
Since I am the one giving the gift...

93
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,039
...I can give it to whomever I want.

94
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,159
Today...

95
00:03:30,159 --> 00:03:32,400
...I'd like everyone to be my witness.

96
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:35,400
That Jialing motorcycle over there...

97
00:03:36,319 --> 00:03:38,240
...I hereby formally present...

98
00:03:38,639 --> 00:03:39,840
...to Comrade Wang Yingrong.

99
00:03:40,319 --> 00:03:41,639
Bravo! Bravo!

100
00:03:44,919 --> 00:03:46,719
Look, it was clearly your good deed.

101
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,240
But they ended up taking the prize.

102
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,240
If only you had gone down to save her sooner!

103
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,080
Mom.

104
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,439
I just found out too.

105
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:54,439
That Sister Yingrong went down to save her first.

106
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,120
You, you, you...

107
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:58,439
My little ancestor.

108
00:03:58,599 --> 00:04:00,680
What a great opportunity you missed.

109
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,479
Even the best opportunity isn't worth dying for.

110
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:04,759
Besides, you didn't see Sister Yingrong.

111
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:06,479
She almost lost her life trying to save her.

112
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,639
If it had been me...

113
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:09,159
...I might have lost my life.

114
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,639
Besides, I'm your baby.

115
00:04:11,639 --> 00:04:12,439
Would you be willing to risk me?

116
00:04:13,759 --> 00:04:14,599
That's true.

117
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,519
My dear boy.

118
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,120
What am I supposed to say to you?

119
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,519
Alright, Mom.

120
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:21,759
You don't need to be jealous.

121
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,160
Neighbors are practically family anyway.

122
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:26,199
Since they have a motorcycle, if you want to use it...

123
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:27,519
...I'll just go borrow it.

124
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:29,759
Who says we're family with the Wangs?

125
00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:31,199
We have a feud with her.

126
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,000
A feud lasting ten lifetimes.

127
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,720
You remember that well.

128
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,279
Alright, alright, I know, Mom.

129
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:44,800
Engineer Zheng.

130
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,639
Do you have any other money-making ideas?

131
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,000
Tell me a few more.

132
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,639
Why?

133
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:51,040
The idea I gave you last time about catching fish,

134
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:52,439
made you quite a bit of money.

135
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,199
Oh, about that thing you mentioned last time.

136
00:04:54,319 --> 00:04:55,720
I haven't had time to do it yet.

137
00:04:56,199 --> 00:04:57,920
But I passed it on to an old customer.

138
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,040
She's already doing it.

139
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:00,480
An old customer?

140
00:05:01,079 --> 00:05:01,800
Alright then.

141
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:03,160
You ask me for ideas,

142
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:04,480
and pass them on to others.

143
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:06,040
Engineer Zheng.

144
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,000
You're well-educated,

145
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:07,680
and capable.

146
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,800
Give your friend a few more ideas.

147
00:05:10,079 --> 00:05:11,040
If I really make money,

148
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:13,000
you can take your pick from my stall.

149
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,040
Wang Yingrong doesn't have a job right now.

150
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,800
It's a good time to put the word out.

151
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:21,279
Let Gossip leak it to Wang Yingrong,

152
00:05:21,639 --> 00:05:23,480
so she can have an income too.

153
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,040
That sounds good.

154
00:05:25,319 --> 00:05:27,000
I'll tell you another good way to make money.

155
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,680
Raising pigs is a profitable path.

156
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,079
Pen them up and raise them.

157
00:05:33,079 --> 00:05:34,319
I guarantee you'll make big money.

158
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,879
Here piggy, piggy.

159
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:38,160
Be good now.

160
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:44,319
I say, has the Wang family

161
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,439
lost all decency?

162
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,120
Who told you to raise this?

163
00:05:49,199 --> 00:05:50,759
What's wrong with me raising pigs?

164
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:51,920
Is it bothering you?

165
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:53,519
You turn down a perfectly good Iron Rice Bowl,

166
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,199
to sell fish and feed pigs.

167
00:05:55,319 --> 00:05:56,720
Just to show you're a country bumpkin?

168
00:05:56,879 --> 00:05:57,959
If you like feeding pigs so much,

169
00:05:58,199 --> 00:05:59,240
move back to the countryside.

170
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,360
Don't be a nuisance here.

171
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,560
Gossip was reliable this time.

172
00:06:02,839 --> 00:06:04,160
She really has started raising pigs.

173
00:06:04,439 --> 00:06:06,279
I'm raising pigs in my own home.

174
00:06:06,279 --> 00:06:07,720
Not in yours.

175
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,000
First catching fish, now catching piglets.

176
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,319
What exactly are you trying to do?

177
00:06:11,319 --> 00:06:12,839
I'm raising pigs to sell for money.

178
00:06:12,959 --> 00:06:14,240
I don't have a job right now,

179
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,680
and I have to make money somehow.

180
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:17,519
Besides,

181
00:06:17,519 --> 00:06:19,720
the Secretary has approved it.

182
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,920
Some people can only watch.

183
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,079
Watch your mouth.

184
00:06:23,079 --> 00:06:24,199
I can't be bothered with you.

185
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,399
As long as Wang Yingrong gets these pigs raised,

186
00:06:30,839 --> 00:06:32,319
and scales up later,

187
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,800
her income won't be any less than at the factory.

188
00:06:42,079 --> 00:06:43,000
Tonight,

189
00:06:43,079 --> 00:06:45,399
you two will have to make do in the pig cage.

190
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:48,360
I'm just too tired.

191
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,279
I promise,

192
00:06:49,319 --> 00:06:50,040
first thing tomorrow morning,

193
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,639
I'll fix up this pen for you.

194
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:06,199
This messing around won't work.

195
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:07,879
Forget it.

196
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:09,079
For the sake of being neighbors,

197
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:10,839
I'll give her a hand.

198
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:43,800
Don't run!

199
00:07:53,319 --> 00:07:55,839
Gotcha!

200
00:07:58,519 --> 00:08:01,040
Gotcha!

201
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:56,039
Pigsty

202
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,759
I haven't finished my pigsty yet

203
00:08:57,799 --> 00:08:58,840
Don't let the pigs run off

204
00:09:03,759 --> 00:09:05,000
You're raising pigs where people live

205
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:05,519
What's wrong with that?

206
00:09:05,639 --> 00:09:06,600
You're not the only one living here

207
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,639
You shrew

208
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,720
So what if I raise pigs?

209
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,279
You country woman, you have no manners

210
00:09:10,279 --> 00:09:12,120
Why did you just build it yourself?

211
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:12,840
It's getting all over the place

212
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,080
You are nothing but a shrew

213
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,240
That pig manure stinks to high heaven

214
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,720
Go ahead, say whatever you want

215
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,960
Just take them back and raise them

216
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,080
Take them to the countryside

217
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,240
You have no morals at all

218
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,159
No manners

219
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,480
Raising pigs is just a whim

220
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,159
Is it something you can just do?

221
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:24,799
You're sick in the head

222
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,240
When have you ever raised pigs?

223
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:28,519
You don't even know what pigs eat

224
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:29,879
How to make pig feed

225
00:09:30,039 --> 00:09:31,559
Why wouldn't I know what they eat?

226
00:09:31,879 --> 00:09:33,240
They eat pigweed

227
00:09:33,519 --> 00:09:35,120
I've asked about all that

228
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,080
Fine, pigs eat pigweed

229
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,919
How do you make feed out of pigweed?

230
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,879
Do you even know how?

231
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,679
If you don't know how

232
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:42,519
Then send the pigs back

233
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:45,799
Pig feed

234
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:50,200
I...

235
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,600
Well...

236
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,080
Wheat bran

237
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,840
Then

238
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:01,639
Chop up the pigweed

239
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,120
Add some... what was it...

240
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,039
Rice bran

241
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,360
Just that

242
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:07,720
Mix it up

243
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,080
And they can eat it

244
00:10:11,879 --> 00:10:12,320
Fine

245
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,080
You think you're so capable

246
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,200
Let's see if you can raise this pig

247
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:17,000
I can raise it

248
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,159
Let go, quick.

249
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,159
If they see us...

250
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:30,960
they'll start talking about you again.

251
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,240
What did you mean just now?

252
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:35,919
Were you helping me?

253
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:37,360
Is it that obvious?

254
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,440
Can't you tell?

255
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,240
The sun must have risen from the west.

256
00:10:43,799 --> 00:10:44,840
Why did you help me?

257
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:47,039
Before, when I sold things for you,

258
00:10:47,039 --> 00:10:48,600
you complained I was meddling.

259
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:54,360
Are you using a new method to take revenge on me?

260
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,399
Comrade Wang Yingrong,

261
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:01,200
you really can't tell good from bad here.

262
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:03,799
Even though our families don't get along,

263
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,720
we are still neighbors after all.

264
00:11:06,279 --> 00:11:07,799
A close neighbor is better than a distant relative.

265
00:11:08,639 --> 00:11:09,960
How can you speculate so maliciously

266
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,039
about my good intentions?

267
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:16,120
The more I think about it,

268
00:11:16,519 --> 00:11:18,240
the stranger it feels.

269
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:28,679
Mom.

270
00:11:30,519 --> 00:11:31,600
Just now, I...

271
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:32,840
saw you and the second Wang child

272
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,000
acting all sneaky.

273
00:11:34,279 --> 00:11:35,080
What were you doing?

274
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:37,440
Do you still want to help her raise pigs?

275
00:11:38,679 --> 00:11:39,240
Mom,

276
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,559
you've misunderstood.

277
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:41,799
Son,

278
00:11:41,879 --> 00:11:43,039
no matter how much you like her,

279
00:11:43,039 --> 00:11:44,399
you have to let it go.

280
00:11:44,879 --> 00:11:46,279
That is a girl from the Wang family.

281
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:48,679
You can't be with her even if it kills you.

282
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:53,799
If that Seductress Wang Yingrong

283
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:55,039
keeps seducing you,

284
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,399
I'll go find her.

285
00:11:57,519 --> 00:11:58,200
Mom,

286
00:11:58,679 --> 00:11:59,159
this matter...

287
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,399
really has nothing to do with Wang Yingrong.

288
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:03,159
Our family's betrothal debt isn't paid off yet.

289
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:05,000
I just wanted to see if Wang Yingrong

290
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,519
can actually succeed at raising pigs.

291
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,519
If raising pigs really makes money,

292
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:09,519
we could also

293
00:12:09,519 --> 00:12:11,200
learn from her and make money raising pigs too.

294
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:12,679
I don't care if you learn to raise pigs,

295
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:13,519
but

296
00:12:13,679 --> 00:12:15,759
you absolutely cannot get involved

297
00:12:15,759 --> 00:12:16,519
with that woman Wang Yingrong.

298
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:17,200
Do you understand?

299
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:18,440
Don't worry.

300
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:20,200
People outside are spreading rumors now,

301
00:12:20,559 --> 00:12:22,120
saying our family has no luck with marriages.

302
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:23,639
I refuse to believe it.

303
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,399
I'll go find that Matchmaker Sun,

304
00:12:25,679 --> 00:12:27,159
to introduce more good girls to you,

305
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,600
settle a marriage sooner,

306
00:12:28,759 --> 00:12:29,840
and shut those mouths outside.
